Let us now discuss the various neutrino–matter interactions that are commonly considered in neutron star merger simulations. Our objective here is not to provide detailed derivations of all interaction rates, but rather to review the reactions that may be taken into consideration and to get reasonable estimates of the scaling of reaction rates with the fluid properties. This will allow us to estimate when different reactions become important to the evolution of the system. Accordingly, for the sake of brevity, the cross-sections and reaction rates presented here sometimes make stronger approximations than what is done in merger simulations. However, for each reaction we provide references to more detailed discussions of these cross-sections. We will also make use of our discussion of the p+e-↔n+νe\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
